castVote(uint256,uint8).details: Casts a vote for a proposal.

params.support: The vote type (0 - Against, 1 - For, 2 - Abstain).

returns._0: The voting weight of the voter.

params._chainId: The chain ID of the current contract.
params._hubContractAddress: The address of the hub contract.
params._hubContractChainId: The chain ID of the hub contract.
params._targetSecondsPerBlock: The target number of seconds per block for block estimation.
params._token: The address of the token contract used for voting.
params._wormholeRelayerAddress: The address of the wormhole automatic relayer contract used for cross-chain communication.

returns._0: A boolean indicating whether the proposal exists.

receiveWormholeMessages(bytes,bytes[],by.details: Receives messages from the Wormhole protocol's relay mechanism and processes them accordingly. This function is intended to be called only by the designated Wormhole relayer.

params.additionalVaas: An array of additional data (not used in this function).
params.deliveryHash: A unique hash representing the delivery of the message to prevent duplicate processing.
params.payload: The payload of the received message.
params.sourceAddress: The address that initiated the message transmission (HelloWormhole contract address).
params.sourceChain: The chain ID of the source contract.
